swt - simple widget toolkit
===========================

BNF:

command ::= DRAW | DUMP | NOOP | QUIT
DUMP    ::= dump | dump id
NOOP    ::= noop
QUIT    ::= quit
DRAW    ::= draw WIDGETS
WIDGETS ::= WIDGET | WIDGETS
WIDGET  ::= HBOX VBOX FRAME LABEL EMBED
HBOX    ::= hbox '(' WIDGETS ')

Installation
------------
Edit config.mk to match your local setup. swt is installed into
/usr/local by default.

Afterwards enter the following command to build and install swt 
(if necessary as root):

    $ make clean install


Running swt
-----------
Simply invoke the 'swt' command with the required arguments.
